# ─── REQUIRED: Backend URL (for the watch page to function) ───
# On Vercel: you can leave this EMPTY — the app auto-detects VERCEL_URL.
# On local dev: defaults to http://localhost:3000/api (same-origin proxy).
# Override only if you want to point to a different backend.
# NEXT_PUBLIC_BACKEND_URL=""

# ─── OPTIONAL: Consumet API instance (for real anime streaming) ───
# Self-host Consumet: https://github.com/consumet/api.consumet.org
# ⚠️ The public api.consumet.org endpoint is DEAD (HTTP 451). Must self-host.
# CONSUMET_URL="https://your-consumet-instance.com"

# ─── OPTIONAL: Cloudflare Worker URL (offloads stream bandwidth from Vercel) ───
# Deploy the Worker in ./cf-worker (see cf-worker/README.md for full instructions).
# When set, the player adds a "cf-proxy" tier between manifest-proxy and
# full-proxy. Streams that enforce Referer headers go through the Worker
# (free tier: 100k req/day, unlimited bandwidth) instead of Vercel,
# saving your 10GB/mo Vercel quota.
#
# Deploy steps:
#   1. npm install -g wrangler
#   2. wrangler login
#   3. cd cf-worker && wrangler deploy
#   4. Copy the resulting https://xan-stream-proxy.<subdomain>.workers.dev URL
#   5. Set NEXT_PUBLIC_CF_WORKER_URL to that URL in Vercel env vars
#   6. Redeploy Vercel
#
# NEXT_PUBLIC_CF_WORKER_URL="https://xan-stream-proxy.your-subdomain.workers.dev"

